other_tests.findings: Initial serum 25-hydroxyvitamin D level was 17 nmol/l, with an appropriate secondary rise in serum parathyroid hormone levels of 9.30 pmol/l. After treatment, serum 25-hydroxyvitamin D level increased to 39 nmol/l, with a decrease in parathyroid hormone levels to 5.60 pmol/l.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Increased serum 25-hydroxyvitamin D level by 129%, and a concomitant appropriate decrease in serum parathyroid hormone level.
